      "side": 1,
      "message": "The sort z bits need to be the most significant. If we don\u0027t consider the drawing-order inversion in the key, there\u0027s no need for the transparent vs. opaque 1-bit portion of the key since the choice of sort z for opaque or transparent draws groups them in the same way, while respecting the clip elements that affect the overall ordering.\n\nThat being said, having the opaque draws go front-to-back based on their inverted painters order seems useful, but it should be part of the \"state\" portion of the key.",
